1 AN ACT relating to utility relocation.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 175 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 Cable operators and broadband providers shall be afforded the same rights as public
6 utilities to reimbursement for the costs associated with relocation of their facilities
7 required in connection with any turnpike project or projects with public highways
8 undertaken pursuant to this chapter.
9 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 175B IS CREATED TO
10 READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 Cable operators and broadband providers shall be afforded the same rights as public
12 utilities to reimbursement for the costs associated with relocation of their facilities
13 required in connection with any project developed by an authority pursuant to this
14 chapter.
15 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 177 IS CREATED TO
16 READ AS FOLLOWS:
